The paper focuses on the development of an intelligent voice navigation system for spreadsheet auditing, which is a human-computer interaction (HCI) problem. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for voice recognition, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Information retrieval (IR) is also mentioned in the paper as a related work, making cs.IR a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of assistive technology for individuals with disabilities, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of a technology, which could be considered as a software engineering (SE) problem, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category.
